  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Food and Non- Food Items to Quarantined Homes in Kailhun</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="2">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Contribute to the containment, disruption and eradication of Ebola in Sierra Leone</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The purpose is to reduce the suffering that victims in the worst hit Ebola communities are experiencing and below are the main activities:
i) Provide food and NFIs to 80 households (approximately 480 individuals) in Kailahun district.  Kailahun is identified as the most vulnerable and isolatedand was first hit by the Ebola virus in Sierra Leone.
ii) Promote behaviour change through radio networks by messaging on the identified gaps in knowledge and behaviour.  This will reach approximately 1,000,000 people in the project location. . The radio messaging will focus on radio discussions where panelists will include Ebola survivors, religious leaders, traditional leaders and activists. Topics of discussion will include modes of transmission of Ebola, the role of physical contact and traditional rites in spreading the disease. News broadcasts, which will include interviews with partners, beneficiaries, local government officials, survivors and local leaders will be another important means of dissemination information on the project.      
iii) Provide personal protective equipment and essential medial supplies to CA partners to reduce the risk.</narrative>
  </description>
